12) CI/CD (GitHub Actions) — pipeline idea
.github/workflows/ci.yml:

on: push

jobs:

lint-frontend (node)

lint-backend (flake8)

test-backend (pytest)

build-docker (docker build)

publish (DockerHub/GHCR) if tag

Also include security scans: Trivy for images, Snyk / npm audit, Bandit for Python.

13) Security checklist (katta va aniq)
.env to‘liq .gitignore qilingan.

API Keys stored in Vault / cloud secrets.

TLS everywhere (Nginx + certbot).

Rate limiting per IP + per-user.

CORS allowlist.

Helmet-like headers for frontend (via Nginx).

SAST: eslint, flake8, bandit, sonarqube.

DAST: OWASP ZAP scan weekly.

DB encryption at rest (prod), field-level encryption for PII.

Audit logs with tamper-evident (hash chain).

Sandbox code execution: enforce CPU/memory/time limits, disable network egress.

Legal: celebrity persona usage must have licenses. Provide disclaimer and opt-in.

Commands to run basic scans:

bash
Copy code
# Trivy scan:
trivy fs ./backend
# Bandit:
bandit -r ./backend
# OWASP ZAP (CI):
# run zap baseline scan against staging URL
14) Monitoring & observability
Export Prometheus metrics from backend (uvicorn metrics, job queue length).

Grafana dashboards: latency, error rate, queue lag, cost per request.

Logging: structured JSON (winston/python logging with JSON), push to Loki/Elasticsearch.

Tracing: OpenTelemetry, Jaeger.

15) Testing & Acceptance Criteria
Unit tests (pytest) coverage target 80%+ for backend core logic.

Integration tests: WebSocket connect → send command → receive response (text+audio+animation).

E2E: Frontend runs (next dev) → connect to local backend via WS → audio plays and 3D anim triggers.

Security tests: SAST + DAST pass baseline.

Performance: support 100 concurrent WS connections (load test with locust).

16) Deployment checklist (prod)
Create prod infra (VPC, subnets, LB).

Deploy backend in k8s with HPA.

Use managed Postgres (if scale) otherwise encrypted RDS/CloudSQL.

Expose via Nginx ingress with TLS.

Setup certbot or managed certs.

Configure monitoring & logging.

Configure backups & restore, DR plan.

17) Legal & privacy notes (muhim)
Celebrity voice/persona: check copyright, voice rights. Provide opt-in toggle and disclaimers.

Data retention policy: user can request deletion; implement GDPR-like endpoints (export/delete).

Secure storage of voice recordings; encrypt in transit and at rest.

18) Qo‘shimcha: lab-sync testing va tuning
Use Rhubarb yoki Montreal Forced Aligner to get phoneme timings.

If using cloud TTS that provides visemes, use them directly.

For local approximation: use audio amplitude envelope to drive mouth_open value and map vowels to visemes.

19) Qo‘llanma: qanday ishni boshlab, qadamlar
Repo klonla.

.env ni .env.example ga mos qilib to‘ldir (OPENAI_API_KEY, S3 creds).

Backend virtualenv yarat, pip install -r requirements.txt.

Frontend npm install.

Docker compose bilan docker-compose up --build sinov.

